The paper deals with removing rain streaks from images, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of a linear model to represent the intensity of each detected rain pixel is a technique commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves image processing techniques, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of optimization techniques to minimize the cost function could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
